<br>
yeah, i admit it is a bit verbose, and some words i could have put into their simpler form. But I was trying, to do something with the work. I wanted this government offical to be drunk, but i wanted also to alert the reader, that this was not just any ordinary drunkard. I used those certian words to capture the particular flavor I was looking for. I could have use, yell or cry out, instead of vociferated, but there was something in vociferated that captivated me.(also it makes people remember this piece or at least captures them in a way. Everyone who had read this piece has commented on that word. So not only does it provide a visual stimulus, but also a cognative one.) In a sense though, I was trying to make it seem like Strembrok, although drunk, was educated. I wanted the reader to assume a sort of educated position, when looking at this fellow, (those who understand what the words mean and those who don't will probably still agree that the narrator is some one of education.) (perhaps this is part of my criticism) In any event, I agree the vocab is a bit steep, but I was just having fun with this piece. I even had one or two words in mind and even constructed sentances around them. <br>
 Actually I didn't use the thesaurus, but i looked up the definition of one word. AP English exposes me to a lot of 'big words' so I am very much familiar with them, whether that is good or bad, i am not sure. Plus I was reading Crime and Punishment simultaneously as I was working on this, so maybe one or two words rubbed off.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/15/02 3:03:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=458.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Eve of Revolution</span><hr size=1> I never said it was a bad thing and you definately pulled off the character...and it wasn't too steep it just makes you bend your brain in a few parts...using big words will make anything stand out....we only normally use about 300 words...anything outside that gets attention...<br>
